  <source>University of Aarhus</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Diabetes is more frequent in women with Turner syndrome. The purpose of this study is to
      see, in what ways the glucose metabolism is different in this study population. The
      hypothesis is that women with Turner Syndrome have an impaired insulin production (beta cell
      function).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
